import pickle
import numpy as np
import torch
import warnings
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import os
import time
import re

from method import NNSolver
import plot_nivel_tanque_new

warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

data_path = os.path.join("datasets", "dc_wss", "dc_wss_dataset_dc5_ex30")

with open(data_path, "rb") as f:
    data = pickle.load(f)

file_name = "08.model_2025-11-23_17-48-33_dc5_samples30_epochs10.pt"
file_path = os.path.join("models", file_name)

m = re.search(r"_samples(\d+)_epochs(\d+)\.pt$", file_name)
if not m:
    raise ValueError(f"Nome de arquivo no segue o padro esperado: {file_name}")

samples = int(m.group(1))
epochs = int(m.group(2))

args = {
    "probType": "dc_wss",
    "hiddenSize": 200,
    "batchSize": 16,
    "useCompl": False,
    "corrMode": "full",
    "qtySamples": samples,
    "epochs": epochs,
    'dc': 5,
}

model = NNSolver(data, args)
model.load_state_dict(torch.load(file_path, map_location=torch.device("cpu")))
model.eval()

inputs_data = [
    torch.tensor([[4, 8, 12, 17, 20, 3, 3, 3, 2.5, 2.5]]),   # FONTINHA
    torch.tensor([[1, 8, 12, 18, 21, 0.1, 1, 3, 2.5, 2.5]]),
    torch.tensor([[1, 8, 12, 18, 21, 2, 1, 3, 2.5, 2.5]]),
    torch.tensor([[1, 8, 12, 18, 21, 3, 1, 3, 2.5, 2.5]]),
    torch.tensor([[0.3, 4, 12, 19, 21, 5, 2, 3, 2, 1]]),
    torch.tensor([[0, 2, 3, 4, 17, 1, 1, 1, 1, 2]]),
]

def pretty_vec(t):
    """Converte tensor para string curta e limpa."""
    return np.array2string(
        t.cpu().numpy(),
        precision=3,
        separator=", ",
        suppress_small=True
    )

print("\n==============================================================")
print("                MODEL EVALUATION SUMMARY")
print("==============================================================")
print(f"Model: {file_name}")
print(f"Samples used in training: {samples}")
print(f"Epochs: {epochs}")
print("==============================================================\n")

for idx, x in enumerate(inputs_data):

    print(f"\n--------------------------------------------------------------")
    print(f"TEST CASE #{idx+1}")
    print(f"--------------------------------------------------------------")

    t0 = time.time()

    with torch.no_grad():
        y = model(x.float())

    elapsed = time.time() - t0

    # Cost, tank levels, violations
    cost = float(data.obj_fn(y, args))
    gt = data.gT(y)[0]
    gTL = data.g_TempLog_Original(y)[0]

    # Summary block
    print(f"Input Variables:")
    print(f"  x = {pretty_vec(x)}")

    print(f"\nPredicted Output (start times + durations):")
    print(f"  y = {pretty_vec(y)}")

    print("\nTank Levels (gT):")
    print(f"  Levels = {pretty_vec(gt[:-1])}")
    print(f"  Final Level @24h = {gt[-1]:.3f}")

    print("\nConstraint Violations:")
    print(f"  Max gT violation      = {torch.max(gt).item():.6f}")
    print(f"  Max g_TempLog violation = {torch.max(gTL).item():.6f}")

    print(f"\nObjective function:")
    print(f"  Total cost =  {cost:.3f}")

    print(f"\nExecution Time: {elapsed:.4f} s")

    # Plot (optional)
    plot_nivel_tanque_new.plot_nivel_tanque_new(
        args,
        y[0],
        cost,
        show=True
    )

print("\n==============================================================")
print("                   END OF ALL TESTS")
print("==============================================================\n")
